# Clean the dataset by renaming relevant columns and extracting the rows with data
# We will first clean the header and focus on total usage per location/account.

# Rename the columns based on what we can infer
data.columns = ['Vendors', 'Account #', 'Location', 'Description', 'Unnamed4', 'Unnamed5', 'Unnamed6', 'Unnamed7', 'Unnamed8', 
                'Jan_2023', 'Feb_2023', 'Mar_2023', 'Apr_2023', 'May_2023', 'Jun_2023', 'Jul_2023', 'Aug_2023', 'Sep_2023',
                'Oct_2023', 'Nov_2023', 'Dec_2023', 'Jan_2024', 'Feb_2024', 'Mar_2024', 'Apr_2024', 'May_2024', 'Jun_2024',
                'Jul_2024', 'Aug_2024', 'Sep_2024', 'Total']

# Remove any rows that do not have account or usage information (i.e., NaN in 'Account #')
cleaned_data = data.dropna(subset=['Account #'])

# Focus on the key columns for the analysis
key_columns = ['Vendors', 'Account #', 'Location', 'Jan_2023', 'Feb_2023', 'Mar_2023', 'Apr_2023', 'May_2023', 
               'Jun_2023', 'Jul_2023', 'Aug_2023', 'Sep_2023', 'Oct_2023', 'Nov_2023', 'Dec_2023', 'Jan_2024', 
               'Feb_2024', 'Mar_2024', 'Apr_2024', 'May_2024', 'Jun_2024', 'Jul_2024', 'Aug_2024', 'Sep_2024', 'Total']

# Group the data by 'Location' and calculate the total usage for each location
usage_per_location = cleaned_data[key_columns].groupby('Location').sum(numeric_only=True)

# Display the summarized data
import ace_tools as tools; tools.display_dataframe_to_user(name="Total Usage per Location", dataframe=usage_per_location)
